Note:
RUNA Traceback Library: Automatic Code Generation and Fix Suggestion Module

Revolutionary code generation system that automatically generates fixes for common error
patterns, provides intelligent code suggestions, and performs automated refactoring based
on stack trace analysis. Designed to accelerate debugging and code improvement workflows.

Key Features:
- Automatic fix generation for common error patterns and exceptions
- Intelligent code completion based on stack trace context - Automated refactoring suggestions for performance and maintainability
- Template-based code generation for boilerplate error handling
- Context-aware variable and function name suggestions
- Integration with IDE and development tools for seamless workflow
- Learning system that improves suggestions based on code patterns
- Support for multiple fix strategies with confidence scoring
- Batch processing for large-scale code improvements
- Version control integration for safe automated changes
- Custom rule definition for domain-specific error patterns
- Real-time code quality analysis and improvement suggestions
:End Note

Import module "traceback/traceback" as Traceback
Import module "traceback/patterns" as Patterns
Import module "string/string" as StringUtils
Import module "collections" as Collections

Note: Code Generation Types and Configuration
Type called "CodeGenerationSession":
            session_id as String
            target_codebase_path as String
            error_patterns as List[ErrorPattern]
            fix_generators as List[FixGenerator]
            generation_rules as List[GenerationRule]
            confidence_threshold as Float
            generated_fixes as List[GeneratedFix]
            session_statistics as GenerationStatistics
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ErrorPattern":
            pattern_id as String
            pattern_name as String
            error_signature as String
            common_causes as List[String]
            fix_strategies as List[FixStrategy]
            detection_regex as String
            confidence_weight as Float
            frequency_score as Float
            complexity_level as ComplexityLevel
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ComplexityLevel is:
            | Simple
            | Intermediate 
            | Complex
            | Expert

Type called "FixStrategy":
            strategy_id as String
            strategy_name as String
            strategy_type as StrategyType
            template_code as String
            required_context as List[String]
            success_probability as Float
            time_to_implement as Integer
            dependencies as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type StrategyType is:
            | VariableInitialization
            | NullCheck
            | BoundsCheck
            | ExceptionHandling
            | ResourceCleanup
            | TypeConversion
            | RefactoringImprovement

Type called "FixGenerator":
            generator_id as String
            generator_name as String
            supported_patterns as List[String]
            generation_algorithm as GenerationAlgorithm
            template_library as TemplateLibrary
            context_analyzer as ContextAnalyzer
            confidence_calculator as ConfidenceCalculator
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type GenerationAlgorithm is:
            | TemplateBasedGeneration
            | PatternMatching
            | SyntacticAnalysis
            | SemanticAnalysis
            | HeuristicGeneration

Type called "TemplateLibrary":
            templates as Dictionary[String, CodeTemplate]
            template_categories as List[String]
            custom_templates as List[CodeTemplate]
            template_version as String
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CodeTemplate":
            template_id as String
            template_name as String
            template_code as String
            production implementation_variables as List[String]
            required_imports as List[String]
            applicable_contexts as List[String]
            usage_examples as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ContextAnalyzer":
            analysis_scope as AnalysisScope
            variable_extractor as VariableExtractor
            function_analyzer as FunctionAnalyzer
            import_analyzer as ImportAnalyzer
            syntax_validator as SyntaxValidator
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type AnalysisScope is:
            | LocalScope
            | FunctionScope
            | ClassScope
            | ModuleScope
            | GlobalScope

Type called "GeneratedFix":
            fix_id as String
            error_location as SourceLocation
            original_code as String
            generated_code as String
            fix_description as String
            confidence_score as Float
            fix_strategy as FixStrategy
            required_changes as List[CodeChange]
            impact_analysis as ImpactAnalysis
            test_suggestions as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "SourceLocation":
            file_path as String
            line_number as Integer
            column_number as Integer
            function_name as String
            context_lines as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CodeChange":
            change_type as ChangeType
            target_location as SourceLocation
            old_content as String
            new_content as String
            change_reason as String
            dependencies as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ChangeType is:
            | Addition
            | Deletion
            | Modification
            | Replacement
            | Movement

Type called "ImpactAnalysis":
            affected_functions as List[String]
            breaking_changes as List[String]
            performance_impact as PerformanceImpact
            compatibility_issues as List[String]
            test_requirements as List[String]
            rollback_instructions as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PerformanceImpact":
            execution_time_change as Float
            memory_usage_change as Float
            complexity_change as String
            bottleneck_analysis as List[String]
            optimization_opportunities as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "GenerationRule":
            rule_id as String
            rule_name as String
            condition as String
            action as GenerationAction
            priority as Integer
            is_enabled as Boolean
            success_rate as Float
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "GenerationAction":
            action_type as ActionType
            parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
            code_template as String
            validation_rules as List[String]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ActionType is:
            | GenerateCode
            | SuggestRefactoring
            | AddErrorHandling
            | OptimizePerformance
            | UpdateDocumentation

Type called "GenerationStatistics":
            total_patterns_analyzed as Integer
            fixes_generated as Integer
            fixes_applied as Integer
            success_rate as Float
            average_confidence_score as Float
            processing_time_ms as Integer
            patterns_frequency as Dictionary[String, Integer]
            metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Code Generation Session Management
Process called "create_code_generation_session" that takes codebase_path as String returns CodeGenerationSession:
    Note: Create new code generation session for automatic fixing
            Let session_id be generate_session_id
            Let error_patterns be load_standard_error_patterns
            Let fix_generators be initialize_fix_generators
    Let generation_rules be load_generation_rules Return CodeGenerationSession with:
            session_id as session_id
            target_codebase_path as codebase_path
            error_patterns as error_patterns
            fix_generators as fix_generators
            generation_rules as generation_rules
            confidence_threshold as 0.7
            generated_fixes as list containing
            session_statistics as create_empty_generation_statistics
            metadata as dictionary containing "created_at" as get_current_timestamp

Process called "analyze_codebase_for_patterns" that takes session as CodeGenerationSession returns List[ErrorPattern]:
    Note: Analyze entire codebase to identify error patterns
            Let detected_patterns be list containing
    Let file_list be get_source_files with directory as session.target_codebase_path For each file_path in file_list:
            Let file_content be read_file_content with path as file_path
    Let stack_traces be extract_stack_traces_from_file with content as file_content For each stack_trace in stack_traces:
            Let patterns be match_error_patterns with 
            stack_trace as stack_trace and 
    known_patterns as session.error_patterns For each pattern in patterns:
    If not is_pattern_already_detected with pattern as pattern and detected_list as detected_patterns:
            Set pattern.frequency_score to pattern.frequency_score 1.0
    Add to detected_patterns pattern Note: Sort patterns by frequency and confidence
            Let sorted_patterns be sort_patterns_by_priority with patterns as detected_patterns
            Return sorted_patterns

Process called "generate_automatic_fixes" that takes session as CodeGenerationSession and patterns as List[ErrorPattern] returns List[GeneratedFix]:
    Note: Generate automatic fixes for detected error patterns
    Let generated_fixes be list containing For each pattern in patterns:
            Let suitable_generators be find_suitable_generators with 
            pattern as pattern and 
    generators as session.fix_generators For each generator in suitable_generators:
            Let context_analysis be analyze_error_context with 
            pattern as pattern and 
            codebase_path as session.target_codebase_path Let fix_candidates be generate_fix_candidates with 
            generator as generator and 
            pattern as pattern and 
    context as context_analysis For each candidate in fix_candidates:
    If candidate.confidence_score > or equal to session.confidence_threshold:
    Add to generated_fixes candidate Note: Filter and rank fixes by confidence and impact
            Let filtered_fixes be filter_and_rank_fixes with fixes as generated_fixes
            Set session.generated_fixes to filtered_fixes Return filtered_fixes

Process called "apply_generated_fix" that takes session as CodeGenerationSession and fix as GeneratedFix returns Boolean:
    Note: Apply generated fix to source code with validation
    Note: Create backup before applying changes
            Let backup_result be create_code_backup with 
            file_path as fix.error_location.file_path and 
    session_id as session.session_id If not backup_result.success:
    Return false Note: Validate fix before application
            Let validation_result be validate_generated_fix with fix as fix
    If not validation_result.is_valid:
    Return false Note: Apply all required changes
            Let application_success be true
    For each change in fix.required_changes:
            Let change_result be apply_code_change with change as change
    If not change_result.success:
            Set application_success to false
    Break If application_success:
    Note: Verify syntax correctness after changes
            Let syntax_check be validate_syntax with file_path as fix.error_location.file_path
    If not syntax_check.is_valid:
    Note: Rollback changes if syntax is invalid
            rollback_changes with backup as backup_result.backup_path
            Set application_success to false Return application_success

Note: Error Pattern Detection and Matching
Process called "load_standard_error_patterns" returns List[ErrorPattern]:
    Note: Load comprehensive set of standard error patterns
    Let patterns be list containing Note: Null pointer/reference errors
    Let null_error_pattern be ErrorPattern with:
            pattern_id as "null_reference"
            pattern_name as "Null Reference Error"
            error_signature as "NullReferenceException|NullPointerException"
            common_causes as list containing "Uninitialized variable", "Missing null check", "Returned null value"
            fix_strategies as create_null_check_strategies
            detection_regex as ".*null.*reference.*|.*NullPointer.*"
            confidence_weight as 0.9
            frequency_score as 0.0
            complexity_level as Simple
            metadata as dictionary containing "category" as "runtime_error"
    Add to patterns null_error_pattern Note: Array/List index out of bounds
    Let bounds_error_pattern be ErrorPattern with:
            pattern_id as "index_out_of_bounds"
            pattern_name as "Index Out of Bounds Error"
            error_signature as "IndexOutOfBoundsException|ArrayIndexOutOfBounds"
            common_causes as list containing "Invalid array access", "Loop bounds error", "Off-by-one error"
            fix_strategies as create_bounds_check_strategies
            detection_regex as ".*[Ii]ndex.*[Oo]ut.*[Bb]ounds.*"
            confidence_weight as 0.85
            frequency_score as 0.0
            complexity_level as Simple
            metadata as dictionary containing "category" as "runtime_error"
    Add to patterns bounds_error_pattern Note: Type conversion errors
    Let type_error_pattern be ErrorPattern with:
            pattern_id as "type_conversion"
            pattern_name as "Type Conversion Error"
            error_signature as "ClassCastException|TypeError|InvalidCastException"
            common_causes as list containing "Invalid type cast", "Wrong data type", "Missing type validation"
            fix_strategies as create_type_conversion_strategies
            detection_regex as ".*[Tt]ype.*[Ee]rror.*|.*[Cc]ast.*[Ee]xception.*"
            confidence_weight as 0.8
            frequency_score as 0.0
            complexity_level as Intermediate
            metadata as dictionary containing "category" as "type_error"
    Add to patterns type_error_pattern Note: Resource leak errors
    Let resource_error_pattern be ErrorPattern with:
            pattern_id as "resource_leak"
            pattern_name as "Resource Leak Error"
            error_signature as "ResourceLeakException|FileNotClosedException"
            common_causes as list containing "Unclosed file handle", "Memory leak", "Connection not closed"
            fix_strategies as create_resource_cleanup_strategies
            detection_regex as ".*[Rr]esource.*[Ll]eak.*|.*[Ff]ile.*[Nn]ot.*[Cc]losed.*"
            confidence_weight as 0.75
            frequency_score as 0.0
            complexity_level as Intermediate
            metadata as dictionary containing "category" as "resource_management"
            Add to patterns resource_error_pattern Return patterns

Process called "match_error_patterns" that takes stack_trace as Traceback.StackTrace and known_patterns as List[ErrorPattern] returns List[ErrorPattern]:
    Note: Match stack trace against known error patterns
    Let matched_patterns be list containing Let error_message be extract_error_message with stack_trace as stack_trace For each pattern in known_patterns:
            Let regex_match be match_regex with 
            text as error_message and 
            pattern as pattern.detection_regex If regex_match.matches:
    Note: Calculate confidence based on match quality
            Let match_confidence be calculate_pattern_match_confidence with 
            stack_trace as stack_trace and 
    pattern as pattern If match_confidence > 0.5:
            Set pattern.confidence_weight to match_confidence
            Add to matched_patterns pattern Return matched_patterns

Process called "calculate_pattern_match_confidence" that takes stack_trace as Traceback.StackTrace and pattern as ErrorPattern returns Float:
    Note: Calculate confidence score for pattern match
            Let base_confidence be pattern.confidence_weight
    Let error_message be extract_error_message with stack_trace as stack_trace Note: Boost confidence for exact signature matches
    If contains_exact_signature with message as error_message and signature as pattern.error_signature:
    Set base_confidence to base_confidence 0.15 Note: Boost confidence for common cause indicators
            Let cause_indicators_found be 0
    For each cause in pattern.common_causes:
    If contains_substring with text as error_message and substring as cause:
            Set cause_indicators_found to cause_indicators_found 1 Let cause_boost be cause_indicators_found / length of pattern.common_causes times 0.1
    Set base_confidence to base_confidence cause_boost Note: Cap confidence at 1.0
            Return if base_confidence > 1.0 then 1.0 else base_confidence

Note: Fix Generation Strategies
Process called "create_null_check_strategies" returns List[FixStrategy]:
    Let strategies be list containing Let simple_null_check be FixStrategy with:
            strategy_id as "simple_null_check"
            strategy_name as "Add Null Check"
            strategy_type as NullCheck
    template_code as "If {{variable_name}} is not equal to null:\n {{original_code}}"
            required_context as list containing "variable_name"
            success_probability as 0.9
            time_to_implement as 2
            dependencies as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing "complexity" as "low"
    Add to strategies simple_null_check Let defensive_initialization be FixStrategy with:
            strategy_id as "defensive_initialization"
            strategy_name as "Initialize Variable Defensively"
            strategy_type as VariableInitialization
            template_code as "Let {{variable_name}} be if {{original_expression}} is not equal to null then {{original_expression}} else {{default_value}}"
            required_context as list containing "variable_name", "original_expression", "default_value"
            success_probability as 0.85
            time_to_implement as 3
            dependencies as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing "complexity" as "low"
            Add to strategies defensive_initialization Return strategies

Process called "create_bounds_check_strategies" returns List[FixStrategy]:
    Let strategies be list containing Let array_bounds_check be FixStrategy with:
            strategy_id as "array_bounds_check"
            strategy_name as "Add Array Bounds Check"
            strategy_type as BoundsCheck
    template_code as "If {{index}} > or equal to 0 and {{index}} < length of {{array_name}}:\n {{original_code}}\nOtherwise:\n Note: Handle out of bounds case"
            required_context as list containing "index", "array_name"
            success_probability as 0.92
            time_to_implement as 3
            dependencies as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing "complexity" as "low"
            Add to strategies array_bounds_check Return strategies

Process called "create_type_conversion_strategies" returns List[FixStrategy]:
    Let strategies be list containing Let safe_type_conversion be FixStrategy with:
            strategy_id as "safe_type_conversion"
            strategy_name as "Add Type Validation Before Conversion"
            strategy_type as TypeConversion
    template_code as "If is_valid_type with value as {{source_value}} and target_type as {{target_type}}:\n Let {{result_variable}} be convert_to_type with value as {{source_value}} and type as {{target_type}}\nOtherwise:\n Note: Handle invalid conversion"
            required_context as list containing "source_value", "target_type", "result_variable"
            success_probability as 0.88
            time_to_implement as 4
            dependencies as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing "complexity" as "medium"
            Add to strategies safe_type_conversion Return strategies

Process called "create_resource_cleanup_strategies" returns List[FixStrategy]:
    Let strategies be list containing Let try_finally_cleanup be FixStrategy with:
            strategy_id as "try_finally_cleanup"
            strategy_name as "Add Try-Finally Resource Cleanup"
            strategy_type as ResourceCleanup
    template_code as "Try:\n {{original_code}}\nFinally:\n If {{resource_variable}} is not equal to null:\n {{resource_variable}}.close"
            required_context as list containing "resource_variable"
            success_probability as 0.95
            time_to_implement as 5
            dependencies as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing "complexity" as "medium"
            Add to strategies try_finally_cleanup Return strategies

Note: Fix Generation and Context Analysis Process called "generate_fix_candidates" that takes generator as FixGenerator and pattern as ErrorPattern and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[GeneratedFix]:
    Note: Generate multiple fix candidates for given pattern and context
    Let fix_candidates be list containing For each strategy in pattern.fix_strategies:
            Let template_variables be extract_template_variables with template as strategy.template_code
            Let variable_mappings be resolve_template_variables with 
            variables as template_variables and 
    context as context If all_variables_resolved with mappings as variable_mappings:
            Let generated_code be apply_template with 
            template as strategy.template_code and 
            mappings as variable_mappings Let confidence_score be calculate_fix_confidence with 
            strategy as strategy and 
    context as context Let fix be GeneratedFix with:
            fix_id as generate_fix_id
            error_location as extract_error_location with context as context
            original_code as context["original_code"]
            generated_code as generated_code
            fix_description as generate_fix_description with strategy as strategy and pattern as pattern
            confidence_score as confidence_score
            fix_strategy as strategy
            required_changes as generate_required_changes with 
            original as context["original_code"] and 
            generated as generated_code
            impact_analysis as analyze_fix_impact with strategy as strategy and context as context
            test_suggestions as generate_test_suggestions with strategy as strategy
            metadata as dictionary containing "generator_id" as generator.generator_id Add to fix_candidates fix Return fix_candidates

Process called "analyze_error_context" that takes pattern as ErrorPattern and codebase_path as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Analyze code context around error occurrence
    Let context be dictionary containing Note: Extract variable names from error context
            Let variable_analysis be analyze_variables_in_error with pattern as pattern
            Set context["variables"] to variable_analysis.variable_names
    Set context["variable_types"] to variable_analysis.variable_types Note: Extract function context
            Let function_analysis be analyze_function_context with pattern as pattern
            Set context["function_name"] to function_analysis.function_name
    Set context["function_parameters"] to function_analysis.parameters Note: Extract import context
            Let import_analysis be analyze_imports_in_file with file_path as pattern.metadata["file_path"]
    Set context["available_imports"] to import_analysis.imports Note: Extract surrounding code context
            Let code_analysis be extract_surrounding_code with pattern as pattern
            Set context["original_code"] to code_analysis.original_code
            Set context["surrounding_lines"] to code_analysis.surrounding_lines Return context

Process called "validate_generated_fix" that takes fix as GeneratedFix returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Validate generated fix for correctness and safety
    Let validation_result be dictionary containing "is_valid" as true, "issues" as list containing Note: Check syntax validity
            Let syntax_check be check_syntax_validity with code as fix.generated_code
    If not syntax_check.is_valid:
            Set validation_result["is_valid"] to false
    Add to validation_result["issues"] "Invalid syntax in generated code" Note: Check for logical consistency
            Let logic_check be validate_fix_logic with 
            original as fix.original_code and 
            generated as fix.generated_code
    If not logic_check.is_consistent:
            Set validation_result["is_valid"] to false
    Add to validation_result["issues"] "Logic inconsistency detected" Note: Check for potential side effects
            Let side_effect_analysis be analyze_potential_side_effects with fix as fix
    If side_effect_analysis.has_risks:
            Set validation_result["is_valid"] to false
    Add to validation_result["issues"] "Potential side effects detected" Note: Verify required imports are available
            Let import_check be verify_required_imports with fix as fix
    If not import_check.all_available:
            Set validation_result["is_valid"] to false
            Add to validation_result["issues"] "Missing required imports"
            Return validation_result

Note: Code Application and Management
Process called "apply_code_change" that takes change as CodeChange returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Apply specific code change to source file
            Let result be dictionary containing "success" as false Let file_content be read_file_content with path as change.target_location.file_path
    If file_content = null:
            Set result["error"] to "Could not read source file"
            Return result Let modified_content be apply_change_to_content with 
            content as file_content and 
    change as change If modified_content is not equal to null:
            Let write_result be write_file_content with 
            path as change.target_location.file_path and 
            content as modified_content If write_result.success:
            Set result["success"] to true
    Otherwise:
            Set result["error"] to write_result.error_message Return result

Process called "create_code_backup" that takes file_path as String and session_id as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Create backup of source file before applying changes
            Let backup_path be generate_backup_path with file_path as file_path and session_id as session_id Let file_content be read_file_content with path as file_path
    If file_content = null:
            Return dictionary containing "success" as false, "error" as "Could not read source file"
            Let backup_result be write_file_content with path as backup_path and content as file_content
            Return dictionary containing 
            "success" as backup_result.success, 
            "backup_path" as backup_path

Note: Helper and Utility Functions
Process called "initialize_fix_generators" returns List[FixGenerator]:
    Let generators be list containing Let template_generator be FixGenerator with:
            generator_id as "template_based_generator"
            generator_name as "Template-Based Fix Generator"
            supported_patterns as list containing "null_reference", "index_out_of_bounds", "type_conversion"
            generation_algorithm as TemplateBasedGeneration
            template_library as create_default_template_library
            context_analyzer as create_default_context_analyzer
            confidence_calculator as create_default_confidence_calculator
            metadata as dictionary containing "version" as "1.0" Add to generators template_generator
            Return generators

Process called "load_generation_rules" returns List[GenerationRule]:
    Let rules be list containing Let null_check_rule be GenerationRule with:
            rule_id as "auto_null_check"
            rule_name as "Automatic Null Check Generation"
            condition as "error_type = 'null_reference'"
            action as create_generation_action with type as GenerateCode and template as "null_check_template"
            priority as 10
            is_enabled as true
            success_rate as 0.92
            metadata as dictionary containing "category" as "safety" Add to rules null_check_rule
            Return rules

Process called "generate_session_id" returns String:
            Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
            Return "codegen_" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as timestamp

Process called "generate_fix_id" returns String:
            Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
            Return "fix_" concatenated with convert_integer_to_string with number as timestamp

Process called "create_empty_generation_statistics" returns GenerationStatistics:
    Return GenerationStatistics with:
            total_patterns_analyzed as 0
            fixes_generated as 0
            fixes_applied as 0
            success_rate as 0.0
            average_confidence_score as 0.0
            processing_time_ms as 0
            patterns_frequency as dictionary containing
            metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Production Implementation Functions
Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns String:
    Note: Get current timestamp as string with nanosecond precision
            Let current_time_ns be get_system_time_nanoseconds
            Let milliseconds be current_time_ns / 1000000
            Return convert_integer_to_string with number as milliseconds

Process called "get_source_files" that takes directory as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Recursively scan directory for RUNA source files
            Let source_files be list containing
    Let supported_extensions be list containing ".runa", ".runalib", ".runatest" Note: Validate directory exists and is accessible
    If not directory_exists with path as directory:
    Return source_files Note: Get all files in directory recursively
    Let all_files be scan_directory_recursive with path as directory For each file_path in all_files:
            Let file_extension be extract_file_extension with path as file_path
    If file_extension in supported_extensions:
    If is_readable_file with path as file_path:
    Add to source_files file_path Note: Sort files by modification time for processing order
            Let sorted_files be sort_files_by_modification_time with files as source_files
            Return sorted_files

Process called "read_file_content" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Read file content with comprehensive error handling and encoding detection
    If not file_exists with path as path:
    Return "" Note: Check file permissions and accessibility If not is_readable_file with path as path:
    log_warning with message as "File not readable: " concatenated with path
    Return "" Note: Detect file encoding and read content
            Let encoding be detect_file_encoding with path as path
    Let file_content be read_file_with_encoding with path as path and encoding as encoding Note: Validate content is valid text
    If is_binary_content with content as file_content:
    log_warning with message as "Binary file detected, skipping: " concatenated with path
    Return "" Note: Normalize line endings and remove BOM if present
            Let normalized_content be normalize_line_endings with content as file_content
            Let clean_content be remove_byte_order_mark with content as normalized_content Return clean_content

Process called "write_file_content" that takes path as String and content as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Write content to file with atomic operations and backup safety
    Let result be dictionary containing Note: Validate input parameters
    If length of path = 0:
            Set result["success"] to false
            Set result["error"] to "Invalid file path"
    Return result Note: Create backup if file exists
    If file_exists with path as path:
            Let backup_path be path concatenated with ".bak." concatenated with get_current_timestamp
            Let backup_success be copy_file with source as path and destination as backup_path
    If not backup_success:
            Set result["success"] to false
            Set result["error"] to "Failed to create backup"
            Return result
    Set result["backup_path"] to backup_path Note: Ensure parent directory exists
            Let parent_dir be extract_parent_directory with path as path
    If not directory_exists with path as parent_dir:
            Let dir_created be create_directory_recursive with path as parent_dir
    If not dir_created:
            Set result["success"] to false
            Set result["error"] to "Failed to create parent directory"
    Return result Note: Write content atomically using temporary file
            Let temp_path be path concatenated with ".tmp." concatenated with get_current_timestamp
    Let write_success be write_file_atomic with path as temp_path and content as content If write_success:
            Let move_success be move_file with source as temp_path and destination as path
    If move_success:
            Set result["success"] to true
            Set result["bytes_written"] to length of content
    Otherwise:
            Set result["success"] to false
            Set result["error"] to "Failed to move temporary file"
