Process called "contains_substring" that takes text as String and substring as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if text contains substring
    If length of text = 0 or length of substring = 0:
            Return false Let text_length be length of text
    Let substring_length be length of substring If substring_length > text_length:
            Return false Let search_limit be text_length - substring_length
    Let index be 0 While index < or equal to search_limit:
            Let matches be true
    Let sub_index be 0 While sub_index < substring_length and matches = true:
            Let text_char be get_character_at_index with text as text and index as (index sub_index)
    Let sub_char be get_character_at_index with text as substring and index as sub_index If text_char is not equal to sub_char:
    Set matches to false Set sub_index to sub_index 1 If matches = true:
            Return true Set index to index 1 Return false

Process called "is_pattern_already_detected" that takes pattern as ErrorPattern and detected_list as List[ErrorPattern] returns Boolean:
