            Return true Set index to index 1 Return false

Process called "sort_patterns_by_priority" that takes patterns as List[ErrorPattern] returns List[ErrorPattern]:
    Note: Sort patterns by frequency score and confidence weight (bubble sort)
            Let sorted_patterns be patterns
    Let n be get_list_length with list as sorted_patterns For i from 0 to (n - 2):
    For j from 0 to (n - 2 - i):
            Let current_pattern be get_list_item with list as sorted_patterns and index as j
    Let next_pattern be get_list_item with list as sorted_patterns and index as (j 1) Note: Calculate priority scores
            Let current_score be current_pattern.frequency_score current_pattern.confidence_weight
    Let next_score be next_pattern.frequency_score next_pattern.confidence_weight If current_score < next_score:
            Set sorted_patterns[j] to next_pattern
            Set sorted_patterns[j 1] to current_pattern Return sorted_patterns

Process called "find_suitable_generators" that takes pattern as ErrorPattern and generators as List[FixGenerator] returns List[FixGenerator]:
    Note: Find generators that support the given pattern
