    If supported_id = pattern.pattern_id:
            Set supports_pattern to true
    Break from loop If supports_pattern = true:
            Add to suitable_generators generator Return suitable_generators

Process called "filter_and_rank_fixes" that takes fixes as List[GeneratedFix] returns List[GeneratedFix]:
    Note: Filter and rank fixes by confidence score
    Let filtered_fixes be list containing Note: Filter fixes by minimum confidence threshold
    For each fix in fixes:
    If fix.confidence_score > 0.5:
    Add to filtered_fixes fix Note: Sort by confidence score (highest first)
    Let n be get_list_length with list as filtered_fixes For i from 0 to (n - 2):
    For j from 0 to (n - 2 - i):
            Let current_fix be get_list_item with list as filtered_fixes and index as j
    Let next_fix be get_list_item with list as filtered_fixes and index as (j 1) If current_fix.confidence_score < next_fix.confidence_score:
            Set filtered_fixes[j] to next_fix
            Set filtered_fixes[j 1] to current_fix Return filtered_fixes

Process called "extract_template_variables" that takes template as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract template variables in {{variable}} format
            Let variables be list containing
            Let template_length be length of template
    Let index be 0 While index < (template_length - 3):
            Let current_char be get_character_at_index with text as template and index as index
    Let next_char be get_character_at_index with text as template and index as (index 1) If current_char = "{" and next_char = "{":
    Note: Found start of variable
            Let var_start be index 2
    Let var_end be find_closing_braces with text as template and start_index as var_start If var_end > var_start:
    Let variable_name be substring with text as template and start as var_start and length as (var_end - var_start) Note: Check if variable already in list
            Let already_exists be false
    For each existing_var in variables:
    If existing_var = variable_name:
            Set already_exists to true
    Break from loop If already_exists = false:
            Add to variables variable_name Set index to var_end 2
    Otherwise:
            Set index to index 1
    Otherwise:
            Set index to index 1 Return variables

Process called "resolve_template_variables" that takes variables as List[String] and context as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Resolve template variables from context
    Let mappings be dictionary containing For each variable in variables:
    Let context_value be get_dictionary_value with dict as context and key as variable and default as null If context_value is not equal to null:
