Note: File System and Content Processing Helper Functions
Process called "directory_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if directory exists and is accessible
            Let path_info be get_file_system_info with path as path
            Return path_info["exists"] and path_info["is_directory"]

Process called "file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file exists and is accessible
            Let path_info be get_file_system_info with path as path
            Return path_info["exists"] and path_info["is_file"]

Process called "is_readable_file" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if file is readable
            Let permissions be get_file_permissions with path as path
            Return permissions["readable"]

Process called "scan_directory_recursive" that takes path as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Recursively scan directory for all files
            Let all_files be list containing
    Let pending_dirs be list containing path While length of pending_dirs > 0:
            Let current_dir be pending_dirs[0]
            Remove from pending_dirs at index 0 Let dir_contents be list_directory_contents with path as current_dir
    For each item in dir_contents:
            Let item_path be current_dir concatenated with "/" concatenated with item
    If directory_exists with path as item_path:
            Add to pending_dirs item_path
    Otherwise if file_exists with path as item_path:
            Add to all_files item_path Return all_files

Process called "extract_file_extension" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Extract file extension from path
            Let last_dot_index be find_last_index_of with text as path and character as "."
    If last_dot_index > or equal to 0:
            Return substring_from_index with text as path and start_index as last_dot_index
            Return ""

Process called "sort_files_by_modification_time" that takes files as List[String] returns List[String]:
    Note: Sort files by modification time (most recent first)
    Let file_times be list containing For each file_path in files:
            Let mod_time be get_file_modification_time with path as file_path
            Let file_info be dictionary containing "path" as file_path, "time" as mod_time
    Add to file_times file_info Note: Sort by modification time (bubble sort for simplicity)
            Let n be length of file_times
    For i from 0 to (n - 2):
    For j from 0 to (n - 2 - i):
    If file_times[j]["time"] < file_times[j 1]["time"]:
            Let temp be file_times[j]
            Set file_times[j] to file_times[j 1]
            Set file_times[j 1] to temp Let sorted_paths be list containing
    For each file_info in file_times:
            Add to sorted_paths file_info["path"] Return sorted_paths

Process called "detect_file_encoding" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Detect file encoding from content
            Let file_size be get_file_size with path as path
    If file_size > 0:
            Let sample be read_file_sample with path as path and bytes as 1024
    If contains_utf8_bom with content as sample:
            Return "utf-8"
    Otherwise if contains_non_ascii with content as sample:
            Return "utf-8"
            Return "ascii"

Process called "read_file_with_encoding" that takes path as String and encoding as String returns String:
    Note: Read file with specified encoding
            Return read_text_file_with_encoding with path as path and encoding as encoding

Process called "is_binary_content" that takes content as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if content contains binary data
            Let binary_chars be 0
    Let total_chars be length of content If total_chars = 0:
    Return false For i from 0 to (total_chars - 1):
            Let char_code be get_character_code_at_index with text as content and index as i
    If char_code < 32 and char_code is not equal to 9 and char_code is not equal to 10 and char_code is not equal to 13:
            Set binary_chars to binary_chars 1 Let binary_ratio be binary_chars / total_chars
    Return binary_ratio > 0.1 Note: More than 10% binary characters

Process called "normalize_line_endings" that takes content as String returns String:
    Note: Normalize line endings to Unix style
            Let normalized be replace_all_occurrences with text as content and old_pattern as "\r\n" and new_pattern as "\n"
            Set normalized to replace_all_occurrences with text as normalized and old_pattern as "\r" and new_pattern as "\n"
            Return normalized

Process called "remove_byte_order_mark" that takes content as String returns String:
    Note: Remove UTF-8 BOM if present
    If length of content > or equal to 3:
            Let first_three be substring with text as content and start as 0 and length as 3
    If first_three = "\ufeff": Note: UTF-8 BOM
            Return substring_from_index with text as content and start_index as 3
            Return content

Process called "split_content_into_lines" that takes content as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Split content into lines
            Return split_string_by_delimiter with text as content and delimiter as "\n"

Process called "line_contains_pattern" that takes line as String and pattern as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if line contains pattern (case-insensitive)
            Let line_lower be convert_to_lowercase with text as line
            Let pattern_lower be convert_to_lowercase with text as pattern
            Return contains_substring with text as line_lower and substring as pattern_lower

Process called "parse_stack_trace_lines" that takes lines as List[String] returns Traceback.StackTrace:
    Note: Parse lines into stack trace object
    If length of lines = 0:
    Return null Note: Create basic stack trace with first line as error message
            Let error_message be lines[0]
    Let stack_frames be list containing For i from 1 to (length of lines - 1):
    If contains_substring with text as lines[i] and substring as "at ":
            Let frame be create_basic_stack_frame with line as lines[i]
            Add to stack_frames frame Return create_stack_trace_object with message as error_message and frames as stack_frames

Process called "trim_whitespace" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Remove leading and trailing whitespace
            Return trim_string_whitespace with text as text

Process called "convert_integer_to_string" that takes number as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert integer to string (already implemented in correlation.runa)
    If number = 0:
            Return "0"
            Let digits be list containing
    Let temp_number be if number < 0 then 0 - number else number While temp_number > 0:
            Let digit be temp_number modulo 10
            Let digit_char be convert_digit_to_char with digit as digit
            Add to digits digit_char at beginning
            Set temp_number to temp_number / 10 Let result be join_string_list with strings as digits
            Return if number < 0 then "-" concatenated with result else result

Process called "convert_digit_to_char" that takes digit as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert single digit to character
    If digit = 0: Return "0"
    If digit = 1: Return "1"
    If digit = 2: Return "2"
    If digit = 3: Return "3"
    If digit = 4: Return "4"
    If digit = 5: Return "5"
    If digit = 6: Return "6"
    If digit = 7: Return "7"
    If digit = 8: Return "8"
    If digit = 9: Return "9"
    Otherwise: Return "0"

Process called "join_string_list" that takes strings as List[String] returns String:
    Note: Join list of strings
            Let result be ""
    For each str in strings:
            Set result to result concatenated with str
            Return result